'''''dínen''''' is a [[Sindarin]] adjective meaning "silent". It is formed from the noun ''[[dîn]]'' ("silence") + adjetive ending ''-en''.<ref>{{PE|17}}, p. 98</ref>

==Examples==
* ''[[Dor Dínen|Dor '''Dínen''']]'' = "Silent Land"
* ''[[Rath Dínen|Rath '''Dínen''']]'' = "Silent Street"
